<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Peru-Crash     02-17 0089</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Peru-Crash,0090</SECOND>
<HEAD>10 Killed When Truck Plunges Off Andean Cliff</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LIMA, Peru (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ten people were killed when a truck hauling
eucalyptus branches plunged off a 330-foot cliff in the Peruvian
Andes, the government said.
   The state news agency Andina said Thursday that the crash
occurred near the northcentral town of Otuzco, 340 miles from Lima.
   No other vehicles were involved in the crash, which police blamed
on recent torrential rains that washed out sections of the crude
dirt and gravel highways in the mountains, Andina reported.
</TEXT>
