<HEAD>Father Who Threatened Suit Over Disciplinary School Haircut Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ELYRIA, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   News reports about a man who threatened to
sue a teacher for cutting his son's hair got the attention of police
who arrested him for failing to complete a court sentence on an
unrelated matter.
   Jack Kotnik, 34, of Elyria, was arrested Wednesday on a bench
warrant issued by Municipal Court Judge John Howard in January 1988
