<FIRST>u i BC-Soviet-NuclearTest     02-17 0138</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Soviet-Nuclear Test,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Soviets Stage Nuclear Test In Central Asian Republic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Soviet Union exploded a nuclear device with a
yield of up to 20 kilotons Friday to investigate what happens during
an atomic explosion, the official Tass news agency reported.
   The underground nuclear test occurred at Semipalatinsk, in the
Soviet Central Asian republic of Kazakkstan, at 7:01 a.m. Moscow
time (11 p.m. EST Thursday), Tass said.
   It said the device exploded had a yield equivalent to 20,000 tons
of TNT, or the power of the U.S. atomic bomb dropped on Hiroshima in
1945.
   Tass said the test was designed ``to check the results of
research in the field of the physics of a nuclear explosion,'' but
gave no more details.
   Radiation levels in and around the Semipalatinsk test site were
normal, Tass said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
