   Following are the annual deficits or surpluses
in U.S. merchandise trade, dating back to 1970:
   1988: $137.3 billion deficit.
   1987: $170.3 billion deficit.
   1986: $155.1 billion deficit.
   1985: $133.6 billion deficit.
   1984: $122.4 billion deficit.
   1983: $64.2 billion deficit.
   1982: $38.4 billion deficit.
   1981: $34.6 billion deficit.
   1980: $31.4 billion deficit.
   1979: $35.9 billion deficit.
   1978: $40.2 billion deficit.
   1977: $37.2 billion deficit.
   1976: $15.7 billion deficit.
   1975: $3.0 billion surplus.
   1974: $9.1 billion deficit.
   1973: $1.3 billion deficit.
   1972: $9.0 billion deficit.
   1971: $4.3 billion deficit.
   1970: $0.8 billion surplus.
