<HEAD>Bush to Nominate Chao as Deputy Transportation Secretary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush said Friday he will nominate
Elaine Chao, the chairman of the Federal Maritime Commission, to be
deputy secretary of transportation.
   If confirmed by the Senate, she would succeed Mary Ann Dawson.
Ms. Chao has been head of the Maritime Commission since 1988 and
previously was deputy administrator of the Maritime Administration
