<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher After Late-Day Rally</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES with closing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices closed higher Friday after an
afternoon rally sparked by strong early Wall Street gains helped the
British market recoup earlier losses.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 9.1
points, or 0.4 percent, at 2,042.9, its best level for the day. The
index moved in negative territory for most of the session, losing as
much as 14.5 points at late morning.
   Volume was thin, with 464.5 million shares traded, down from
Thursday's 644.1 million shares.
   Trading activity was light amid what dealers said was uncertainty
about the market's direction. A slight amount of buying interest
late in the day sparked widespread markups, they said.
   The market shrugged off a sharp rise in British inflation. There
also was scant reaction to a U.S. trade report that fell within
market expectations, dealers said.
