<HEAD>Apple Announces Resignation Of Vice President</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CUPERTINO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Apple Computer Inc. has accepted the
resignation of Charles Berger, its vice president of integrated
systems, the eighth top executive to leave the company during its
recent reorganization.
   Berger, 35, joined Sun Microsystems Inc., of Mountain View, as
vice president of product marketing in the entry systems group.
   Berger will focus on increasing Sun's share of markets dominated
by Apple, said Tim Bajarin, executive vice president with the market
research company Creative Strategies Research International of Santa
Clara.
   ``It's a major loss for Apple and a major coup for Sun,'' Bajarin
said.
