<FIRST>d f BC-PetroleumReview     02-17 0775</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Petroleum Review,0484</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Total crude runs to stills averaged 13,150,000
barrels daily during the week ended Friday, Feb. 10, the American
Petroleum Institute reported Thursday. This compared with 13,429,000
barrels daily in the previous week and 12,739,000 barrels daily a
year ago.
   Crude runs east of California averaged 10,734,000 barrels daily
compared with 10,824,000 the previous week and 10,330,000 a year ago.
   Motor gasoline production for the latest week amounted to
6,681,000 barrels a day, compared with 6,912,000 barrels a day in
the previous week and 6,641,000 a day a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline production was 5,513,000 a day
compared with 5,713,000 a day last week and 5,552,000 a day a year
ago.
   Motor gasoline stocks at the end of the latest week were
245,844,000 barrels, versus 243,877,000 a week earlier and
236,560,000 a year ago.
   East of California motor gasoline stocks totaled 211,890,000
barrels compared with 209,102,000 in the previous week and
203,396,000 barrels last year.
   Daily average gross crude oil and lease condensate production for
the week ended Friday was 7,957,000 barrels compared with 8,338,000
last year.
   Crude oil stocks totaled 324,873,000 barrels at the close of last
week, against 332,433,000 a week previous and 333,174,000 a year ago.
   East of California crude stocks amounted to 247,435,000 barrels,
compared with 255,445,000 a week earlier.
   Daily imports east of California for the week ended Friday were
crude oil, 5,297,000 barrels, residual fuel oil, 519,000, distillate
fuel oil, 450,O00, and others 2,106,000, a total of 8,656,000
barrels.
   California imports were: crude oil 210,000 barrels, and products
74,000, a total of 284,000 barrels, for a grand total of 8,656,000.
   For the four weeks, daily imports east of California were crude
oil 5,446,000 barrels, residual fuel oil 368,000, distillate fuel
oil 177,000, and others 803,000, for a total of 6,794,000 barrels.
   For the four weeks, California daily imports averaged for crude
oil 226,000 barrels, products 62,000, a total of 288,000 barrels,
for a grand total of 7,082,000.
   The following table shows comparative daily production of the
other principal refined products for the U.S. as a whole and east of
California. Also shown are the comparative stock totals for certain
refined products.
