<FIRST>r f BC-GAFMeeting     02-17 0148</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-GAF Meeting,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>GAF Corp. Reschedules Shareholders Meeting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WAYNE, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   GAF Corp. said Thursday its annual meeting had
been rescheduled to March 2 to give shareholders time to review
proxy materials, which include revised financing for a proposed
management-led buyout of the company.
   The meeting originally was set for Feb. 22.
   Shareholders are to vote on the proposed $53-a-share cash and
securities buyout led by Samuel J. Heyman, GAF's chairman and chief
executive.
   Under the revised financing arrangement, Heyman will buy $48
million of notes and an additional $2 million in preferred stock,
GAF said.
   Meanwhile, the chemical and building-materials company and James
T. Sherwin, its vice president, are standing trial in Manhattan on
charges of stock manipulation, securities fraud, wire fraud
conspiracy and other crimes for their alleged attempt to boost the
price of Union Carbide, the target of a failed GAF takeover attempt.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
